s edited collection uncover the multitude of actors , beyond the sending and receiving countries and migrants themselves, who play a role in creating, transmitting, transforming and utilizing the value embedded in international health migrants.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEmigration and immigration. 0aFeminism. 0aGlobalizationxEconomic aspects. 0aLabor mobility. 0aMedical personnelxEmploymentzForeign countries. 0aMedical personnelxSupply and demandzForeign countries. 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / General.2bisacsh  abrain drain.  ahealth worker migration.  aimmigration and professional credentials.  aimmigration and skills.  ainternationally educated health professionals.  ainternationally educated nurses.1 aAdekola, Sheri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAntonipillai, Valentina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAtanackovic, Jelena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaumann, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBornat, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBourgeault, Ivy Lynn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChikanda, Abel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConnell, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrea-Arsenio, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrush, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEnnis, Crystal A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenry, Caitlin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenry, Leroi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relato